---
import Accordion from "../ui/Accordion.astro"
import ShowcaseSection from "./ShowcaseSection.astro"
---

<ShowcaseSection id="accordion" title="Accordion">
  <Fragment slot="description">
    Native <code class="rounded bg-(--color-bg-surface) px-1">&lt;details&gt;</code>/<code
      class="rounded bg-(--color-bg-surface) px-1">&lt;summary&gt;</code
    > accordion — no JS. Multiple items can be open simultaneously. Pass <code
      class="rounded bg-(--color-bg-surface) px-1">open</code
    > to expand by default.
  </Fragment>

  <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-6">
    <Accordion title="What is Core Boilerplate?" open>
      A production-ready Astro 7 + Tailwind CSS v4 starter with WCAG AA enforced at build time,
      100/100 Lighthouse scores, and a full UI component library.
    </Accordion>

    <Accordion title="Do I need to credit the author?">
      No — Core Boilerplate is MIT-licensed. Use it in personal and commercial projects without
      attribution.
    </Accordion>

    <Accordion title="Can I add my own components?">
      Absolutely. Every component lives in <code
        class="rounded bg-(--color-bg-surface) px-1 font-mono text-xs">src/components/ui/</code
      > — just drop a new <code class="rounded bg-(--color-bg-surface) px-1 font-mono text-xs"
        >.astro</code
      > file there.
    </Accordion>

    <Accordion title="Is dark mode supported?">
      Yes — all color tokens have dark-mode overrides in <code
        class="rounded bg-(--color-bg-surface) px-1 font-mono text-xs">src/config.ts</code
      >. The <code class="rounded bg-(--color-bg-surface) px-1 font-mono text-xs">ThemeToggle</code> component
      handles switching.
    </Accordion>
  </div>
</ShowcaseSection>
